00:32:46.390 --> 00:32:48.348
I love, which we saved
for last, because that's

00:32:48.348 --> 00:32:49.810
the easiest thing to experience.

00:32:49.810 --> 00:32:50.600
DAN STONE: Yeah.

00:32:50.600 --> 00:32:52.391
DANIEL HANDLER: And
we'll all be plastered.

00:32:53.780 --> 00:32:58.120
And the movie is a
Mexican melodrama.

00:32:58.120 --> 00:32:59.340
Here it is on DVD.

00:33:01.850 --> 00:33:03.161
We both brought this.

00:33:03.161 --> 00:33:04.160
I don't really know why.

00:33:04.160 --> 00:33:05.035
So we can hold it up.

00:33:05.035 --> 00:33:05.780
See?

00:33:05.780 --> 00:33:07.579
And you thought I was lying.

00:33:07.579 --> 00:33:09.870
DAN STONE: You carry it with
you everywhere, don't you?

00:33:09.870 --> 00:33:10.690
DANIEL HANDLER: I kind of do.

00:33:10.690 --> 00:33:11.500
DAN STONE: He loves this movie.

00:33:11.500 --> 00:33:12.111
And I do, too.

00:33:12.111 --> 00:33:12.610
It's great.

00:33:12.610 --> 00:33:14.420
But I didn't know it until
you told me about it.

00:33:14.420 --> 00:33:15.586
DANIEL HANDLER: No one does.

00:33:15.586 --> 00:33:18.510
And it's nice about having
a favorite movie that no one

00:33:18.510 --> 00:33:20.940
else has seen is you
get to show to them.

00:33:20.940 --> 00:33:27.630
And I saw this movie
for the first time

00:33:27.630 --> 00:33:29.800
in the mid-'90s at
the Castro Theater,

00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:32.980
and I moved to New York, and
it started playing in New York

00:33:32.980 --> 00:33:34.490
right after I moved there.

00:33:34.490 --> 00:33:37.940
And so I saw it again
with a friend of mine.

00:33:37.940 --> 00:33:39.570
I saw two showings in a row.

00:33:39.570 --> 00:33:42.614
I saw it with one
friend, and then

00:33:42.614 --> 00:33:44.155
I said goodbye to
my friend, and then

00:33:44.155 --> 00:33:45.940
I just waited
outside the theater,

00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:48.300
and my other friend came,
and we went and saw it again.

00:33:48.300 --> 00:33:49.790
And I didn't admit
it, because it

00:33:49.790 --> 00:33:51.415
was going to be too
crazy to say that I

00:33:51.415 --> 00:33:53.415
wanted to show
people this movie.

00:33:53.415 --> 00:33:55.190
And it's great.

00:33:55.190 --> 00:33:58.130
"La Aventurera," or
"The Adventurist."

00:33:58.130 --> 00:34:01.103
It's a 1950s kind
of noir melodrama.

00:34:01.103 --> 00:34:02.320
It's Mexican.

00:34:04.652 --> 00:34:06.860
I'm going to say the first
five minutes of the movie,

00:34:06.860 --> 00:34:07.950
because it's so insane.

00:34:10.190 --> 00:34:13.580
Our hero, Elena,
skips down the stairs.

00:34:13.580 --> 00:34:15.790
And we should say
that our heroine

00:34:15.790 --> 00:34:18.789
is played by this
talentless actress.

00:34:18.789 --> 00:34:21.080
She can't act, and she can't
sing, and she can't dance,

00:34:21.080 --> 00:34:23.243
and she does all of
them in the movie.

00:34:23.243 --> 00:34:24.659
And so the movie
is also this kind

00:34:24.659 --> 00:34:28.980
of love story from the
director, who, big surprise,

00:34:28.980 --> 00:34:30.320
was in love with this woman.

00:34:30.320 --> 00:34:32.710
So he's made this movie
around this woman.

00:34:32.710 --> 00:34:35.320
And he just says, well,
I'm taking it as a given

00:34:35.320 --> 00:34:37.440
that everyone finds
this woman irresistible.

00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:39.860
And find her utterly
irresistible.

00:34:39.860 --> 00:34:42.679
So I love that it's this
movie where he's like, right?

00:34:42.679 --> 00:34:43.179
Am I right?

00:34:43.179 --> 00:34:44.389
The best dancer in the world.

00:34:44.389 --> 00:34:45.765
And you're like, mm, no.

00:34:49.230 --> 00:34:53.550
But she is taking dance
classes and living

00:34:53.550 --> 00:34:55.639
with her kind of
uptight parents--

00:34:55.639 --> 00:34:59.420
her sensitive father
and her brusque mother.

00:34:59.420 --> 00:35:04.610
And a man-- a family
friend-- comes up

00:35:04.610 --> 00:35:06.210
to take her to dance class.

00:35:06.210 --> 00:35:08.010
And the mom says,
no, I don't want you

00:35:08.010 --> 00:35:09.040
with that family friend.

00:35:09.040 --> 00:35:09.730
He flirts with you too much.

00:35:09.730 --> 00:35:10.710
You go by yourself.

00:35:10.710 --> 00:35:14.160
So she goes by herself to dance
class, and when she gets back,

00:35:14.160 --> 00:35:16.910
she finds her mother in the
arms of the family friend.

00:35:16.910 --> 00:35:23.000
[GASP] And then the father
gets home and learns this,

00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:25.590
and goes into the study
and shoots himself.

00:35:25.590 --> 00:35:29.550
And then Elena leaves the
house, and you get a flashback.

00:35:29.550 --> 00:35:30.961
You've gotten so many things--

00:35:30.961 --> 00:35:32.335
DAN STONE: This
is in 10 minutes.

00:35:32.335 --> 00:35:32.800
DANIEL HANDLER: That's
one of my favorite things.

00:35:32.800 --> 00:35:34.860
In the first eight
minutes of the film,

00:35:34.860 --> 00:35:38.566
there's a flashback to
what you've just seen,

00:35:38.566 --> 00:35:40.440
because there's so much
shocking information.

00:35:40.440 --> 00:35:42.023
She's in the street
being like, oh no!

00:35:42.023 --> 00:35:45.010
And then it shows the
scene of it going on.

00:35:45.010 --> 00:35:46.930
And she's like, I
can't handle it!

00:35:46.930 --> 00:35:51.330
And I love that it mimics
your reaction as the viewer.

00:35:51.330 --> 00:35:53.380
Because you're like, I
can't handle any of it.

00:35:53.380 --> 00:35:54.060
This is insane.

00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:57.690
Anyway, she ends up in
a white slavery thing.

00:35:57.690 --> 00:35:58.481
That's complicated.

00:36:02.129 --> 00:36:03.920
She ends up kind of in
a white slavery ring

00:36:03.920 --> 00:36:06.602
run by the mother of
her subsequent lover.

00:36:06.602 --> 00:36:07.310
It's complicated.

00:36:09.120 --> 00:36:12.430
But what we're going to show
is one of the dance scenes,

00:36:12.430 --> 00:36:15.360
which, for me, because
it's the third drink,

00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:18.800
I think we all want to stare
rapturously at this movie that

00:36:18.800 --> 00:36:23.022
is a love story about an
irresistible woman who's

00:36:23.022 --> 00:36:25.230
utterly resistible for
everyone else but the director

00:36:25.230 --> 00:36:25.990
of the film.

00:36:25.990 --> 00:36:27.448
DAN STONE: You
know, it's funny you

00:36:27.448 --> 00:36:30.480
say that, because everything
I've read about this film,

00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:32.010
everyone just complements her.

00:36:32.010 --> 00:36:33.924
I found her to be not--

00:36:33.924 --> 00:36:36.215
DANIEL HANDLER: She's the
Elizabeth Berkley of her day,

00:36:36.215 --> 00:36:37.710
I think.

